.fi
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Iterative calculation of sample variance
\&\s-2\u[1]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[2]\d\s+2 [$\sigma_n^2$]
according to the formula
\fBEquation 1.36. \fR \&\s-2\u[3]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[4]\d\s+2 \e[ \esigma_n^2 = \efrac{1}{n} \esum_{i = 1}^n (x_i \- \emu_n)^2 = \efrac{n\-1}{n} \esigma_{n\-1}^2 + \efrac{1}{n\-1}(x_n \- \emu_n)^2\&. \e] .RE
where
\fBEquation 1.37. \fR \&\s-2\u[5]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[6]\d\s+2 \e[ \emu_n = \efrac{1}{n} \esum_{i = 1}^n x_i\&. \e] .RE
is the estimate of the sample mean and
\&\s-2\u[7]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[8]\d\s+2 [$n$]
is the number of samples\&.
.PP
Note that the sample variance is not defined for
\&\s-2\u[9]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[10]\d\s+2 [$n <= 1$]\&.
.PP
A simplification can be obtained by the approximate recursion
\fBEquation 1.38. \fR \&\s-2\u[11]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[12]\d\s+2 \e[ \esigma_n^2 \eapprox \efrac{n\-1}{n} \esigma_{n\-1}^2 + \efrac{1}{n}(x_n \- \emu_n)^2\&. \e] .RE
because the difference
\fBEquation 1.39. \fR \&\s-2\u[13]\d\s+2.sp .RS 4 [IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[14]\d\s+2 \e[ \eleft(\efrac{1}{n\-1} \- \efrac{1}{n}\eright)(x_n \- \emu_n)^2 = \efrac{1}{n(n\-1)}(x_n \- \emu_n)^2\&. \e] .RE
converges to zero as
\&\s-2\u[15]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[16]\d\s+2 [$n \rightarrow \infty$]\&. However, for small
\&\s-2\u[17]\d\s+2[IMAGE]\&\s-2\u[18]\d\s+2 [$ n $]
the difference can be non\-negligible\&.
